The paper deals with parameterized complexity of graph coloring problems, which are typically studied in the areas of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), and graph theory (cs.GT). The algorithms and kernels presented in the paper involve techniques such as randomized algorithms, kernelization, and compression, which are commonly used in the areas of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
